


2004-04-23    <mm@KETCHTOO>

  New features: 
   - generate a WSDL file from the Lisp definition of a service
   - examine the namespace configuration in a WSDL file and
       choose a namespace-to-package mapping

  Enhancements and corrections:
   - we can now parse and generate interfaces for  149 of 157 RPC 
       definitions on xmethods.com
   - summary information in generated client or server file 
   - soap-message-client can now specify a proxy

Details:
	
soap-message-client    NEW keyword argument: start   

soap-message-server    NEW keyword arguments: name service-name url port-name 
                                              binding-name

NEW accessors for soap-connector
   soap-port-name
   soap-binding-name
   soap-service-name

enable-soap-server server &key &allow-other-keys

disable-soap-server server &key &allow-other-keys

start-soap-server server &key new start enable &allow-other-keys

stop-soap-server  server &key disable &allow-other-keys

wsdl-server-names wsdl-file-connector

make-client-interface    make-server-interface
   NEW keyword arguments: port if-missing-package

encode-wsdl-file file &key namespaces servers target name (if-exists :supersede)

decode-wsdl-namespaces &key file string uri other-pk base-ns

